  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">In Angola, climate change provides a major threat to poor farming communities seeking to rebuild their lives after the war. Christian Aid works with thousands of families to better understand how they can adapt their farming practices to cope with climate change. This largely involves using more drought resistant crops, and changing soil and water conservation practices. As a result, farming communities are becoming better able to withstand the impact of climate change and to earn a decent livelihood for themselves and their families</narrative>
